data.comment: Pavil, the Pudgy Artist of the Streets
data.metadata:
{"description":"I first got to know Pavil at Pudgy Asia. With 8,888 Pudgy Penguins out there, it‚Äôs not always easy for us to know everyone!

However, i recognized him instantly because i had seen so much of his spray painted wall art before. he is truly like a modern day bard. he brightens up the streets by filling ordinary walls with murals of Igloo, Abstract, Pudgy, and more.

I believe the secret behind his vibrant art lies in his physical health. Pavil constantly trains with triathlons to maintain a healthy body. socrates‚Äô famous quote, "sound mind in a sound body", describes him perfectly.

By the way, why can‚Äôt I attach photos on the Ethos project? You really need to see the Bearish, Fugz, Abstrer, and Pudgy drawings he painstakingly created stroke by stroke

My personal wish is that he visits Korea someday to paint a mural here. He is an artist friend I really look forward to getting to know better!

Love you, Pudgy Fam Pavil!"}

{"description":"If you‚Äôve spent any time around AbstractChain or Raiku, you‚Äôve almost certainly seen MIC. He‚Äôs one of those accounts that feels ever present always replying, amplifying updates, and injecting energy into conversations the moment something happens.

On AbstractChain, he‚Äôs widely known as a Giga Chad, not in the meme only sense, but as someone who consistently shows up for the ecosystem. Updates like Portal V2, Pudgy Penguins SBT drops, or community announcements don‚Äôt just pass by his timeline he actively helps them circulate. His tone is light, humorous, and fast, which makes Abstract‚Äôs consumer first culture feel alive rather than corporate.

At the same time, he plays a similar role in the Solana side through Raiku, where he‚Äôs embraced the tongue in cheek title of ‚ÄúChief Feet Guy.‚Äù It‚Äôs a joke, but also a signal of how he operates approachable, culture first, and deeply embedded in the social layer of Web3 rather than just the technical one.

Most of his activity lives in replies rather than long posts, but that‚Äôs part of his value. He connects people, reacts instantly, and keeps momentum going. He‚Äôs reliably positive, avoids drama, and never leans into misleading hype or sketchy behavior which quietly matters a lot in crypto spaces.

MIC isn‚Äôt trying to be an analyst or a prophet. He‚Äôs a community amplifier who understands that ecosystems grow through vibes, visibility, and consistency. If you‚Äôre looking for someone who genuinely contributes to Web3 projects by being present and supportive every single day, he‚Äôs exactly that type of contributor."}

{
  "description": "His Web 3.0 story is split into two parts: Minebuu the Trader, and Minebuu the Airdrop Hunter. i will recount both narratives here.

As a trader, he was truly exceptional. he was an elite figure who operated within South Korea‚Äôs largest community, DC Inside's "Cryptocurrency Gallery," where he posted profit verifications and even led a trading team that ranked number one globally, drawing widespread admiration.

However, he suddenly vanished, leading many people to speculate and track his whereabouts, believing he had been liquidated for 20 billion KRW(approximately 15 million USD). days later, Minebuu confirmed he had indeed been liquidated for 20 billion KRW. With just the remaining 500 million KRW(approximately 375,000 USD) left, he bought every single 'Orbit Chain' token he could, which was trading at just 1 KRW per token at the time.

Astonishingly, in just one month, 'Orbit Chain' soared to 4,000 KRW, achieving the miracle of fully recovering the 20 billion KRW he had lost in futures trading. This is the story of Minebuu the Trader as I know it.

The other side, Minebuu the Airdrop Hunter, carried out his activities based on meticulous research that paralleled his trading prowess. he actively discovered countless projects like TreasureDAO, Succinct, and Abstract. Amidst his progress.

He once had a private chat with me because not many people were joining his Abstract Portal streaming sessions.

Me : Minebuu, if you have some free time now, which Airdrop task would you focus on?

Minebuu : Do Abstract.

Me : Then, what are your thoughts on the flood of negative news caused by the Ethereum Foundation's massive sale of $ETH?

Minebuu : I believe that issue will be resolved when the price of $ETH goes up. Ethereum is actively accomplishing numerous things even now, and to truly move into Web 3.0, you must come through Ethereum. As for the $ETH sale, I think it's because they have internal costs they need to cover, and I don't see it as a major problem. And also, do Lighter Perp-dex!

After hearing his words directly, a powerful conviction ran through me. armed with strong faith, I have since accumulated Abstract, Lighter, and $ETH, which has resulted in significant profits.

Perhaps the reason i am so committed to Abstract is entirely due to his advice. The insight of a Giga Chad is truly on another level."
}

data.comment: Sayyes? The Man Who Led Me to the Path of a Giga Chad!
data.metadata:
{
  "description": ""Sayyes" in Korean, this can be interpreted as "I can do anything, no matter what." True to his name, he is incredibly wealthy. as a member of the "Lonely Trader" Telegram group, he is literally a legendary trader... In his prime, there were times he earned 100 million KRW in a single day.

Yet, for some reason... he jumped into the world of Abstract and reached the Platinum tier in the shortest time recorded in Korea. he spent over 400 million KRW! Since he clearly has the capital, he aggressively participated in Abstract dApps and shared his reviews with us.

He personally demonstrated that Abstract XP isn't gained simply by spending a vast amount of money, but by securing high rankings efficiently to maximize XP gain.

Additionally, alongside Joy and Minbuu, he streams the video series "I Buy Coins Alone" every week on the Abstract Portal, drawing many people into the world of Abstract. Based on these contributions, he also acquired the Giga Chad title the most prestigious role in Abstract in a short period.

Perhaps he looked kindly upon my hard work... He passed on his methods for obtaining the Giga Chad role, encouraging me by saying, "Someone who works as hard as you do in Korea deserves this role!" He taught me strategies like deep diving into a single Abstract dApp to educate users and becoming an ambassador. i am still deeply grateful to Sayyes for his mentorship.

I also met him in person at KBW 2025 and got his autograph. to give you a real life review: he is quite fashionable and stylish. he has high social intelligence and brings laughter to many people.

In fact, it is no exaggeration to say that I received the Giga Chad role thanks to his advice.

Thank you so much for being with Abstract and with me!"
}

"Sayyes" in Korean can be interpreted as "I can do anything, no matter what." True to his name, he is incredibly wealthy. As a member of the "Lonely Trader" Telegram group, he is literally a legendary trader... In his prime, there were times he earned 100 million KRW in a single day.

Yet, for some reason... he jumped into the world of Abstract and reached the Platinum tier in the shortest time recorded in Korea. He spent over 400 million KRW! Since he clearly has the capital, he aggressively participated in Abstract dApps and shared his reviews with us.

He personally demonstrated that Abstract XP isn't gained simply by spending a vast amount of money, but by securing high rankings efficiently to maximize XP gain.

Additionally, alongside Joy and Minbuu, he streams the video series "I Buy Coins Alone" every week on the Abstract Portal, drawing many people into the world of Abstract. Based on these contributions, he also acquired the Giga Chad title, the most prestigious role in Abstract, in a short period.

Perhaps he looked kindly upon my hard work... He passed on his methods for obtaining the Giga Chad role, encouraging me by saying, "Someone who works as hard as you do in Korea deserves this role!" He taught me strategies like deep diving into a single Abstract dApp to educate users and becoming an ambassador. I am still deeply grateful to Sayyes for his mentorship.

I also met him in person at KBW 2025 and got his autograph. To give you a real-life review: he is quite fashionable and stylish. He has high social intelligence and brings laughter to many people.

In fact, it is no exaggeration to say that I received the Giga Chad role thanks to his advice.

Thank you so much for being with Abstract and with me!
